ess, how to feel about life.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bestofneworleans.com/dispatch/2004-04-13/feat.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040524000602/http://www.bestofneworleans.com/dispatch/2004-04-13/feat.html |archivedate=May 24, 2004 |title=Welcome to the Best of New Orleans! Feature 04 13 04 |publisher=BestOfNewOrleans.com |accessdate=July 9, 2012}}</ref> Internationally, Batiste has served as leader of the daily [[Moldejazz]] parade since 2000. He was king of the [[Krewe du Vieux]] for 2003.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kreweduvieux.org/past.html |title=Krewe du Vieux |publisher=Krewe du Vieux |date=February 4, 2012 |accessdate=July 9, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170704075955/http://www.kreweduvieux.org/past.html |archive-date=July 4, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{reflist}}\n*{{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040524000602/http://www.bestofneworleans.com/dispatch/2004-04-13/feat.html |date=May 24, 2004 |title=''Lionel of All Trades''. BestofNewOrleans.com, April 13, 2004 }}.\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100208024119/http://blogofneworleans.com/blog/2010/02/05/matters-of-great-importance-uncle-batistes-stolen-drum/ ''Matters of Great Importance: Uncle Batiste\u2019s Stolen Drum''. BestofNewOrleans.com, February 5, 2010.]\n* [http://www.bestofneworleans.com/blogofneworleans/archives/2012/07/08/uncle-lionel-batiste-1931-2012 Gambit Weekly obit]\n* [https://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/17/us/new-orleans-celebrates-life-of-lionel-batiste.html?_r=1&src=me&ref=general New Orleans Celebrates the Life of a Bandleader]. ''[[New York Times]]'', July 17, 2012.\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.nola.com/music/index.ssf/2012/07/uncle_lionel_batiste_treme_bra.html Uncle Lionel Batiste, Treme Brass Band bass drummer, dies] Keith Spera, Times-Picayune\n*{{IMDb name|id=3918668}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Batiste, Lionel}}\n[[Category:Jazz musicians from New Orleans]